                                <support><p>The upper portion of a marble stele, of which the lower part is wholly lost. Minor damage to the upper edge, and of the surviving portion the lower right corner is broken. The stele has a moulding framing the text, parallel with the vertical sides, and in a rounded semi-circle at the top; what may be two acroteria-like 'wings' or 'horns' are more lightly incised upper left and upper right.</p>
